I'll share another secret tip during a #Bitcoin bull run: 

When trading large caps you put your buy orders just BELOW everyone's support,

as large players hunt for your stop loss to take you out, then price pumps.

But here's what people don't know: 

When trading low caps you should put your buy orders just ABOVE everyone's support.

Why?
 
Larger players don’t trade low caps. 

If you wait for support, you will get front run and miss your entry by a small % as price pumps.

Like and follow if you want more of these practical tips.

The blockchain technology was described in 1991 by the research scientist Stuart Haber and W. Scott Stornetta. They wanted to introduce a computationally practical solution for time-stamping digital documents so that they could not be backdated or tampered. As countries embracing #Bitcoin and cryptocurrencies continue to grow, Indonesia might be the next nation to open its doors wide for this innovative and lucrative economic sector.

According to Governor Ridwan Kamil, Bitcoin mining is a focal point in the government's study on how Bitcoin adoption can "benefit the country's population." 1661719463874424833.text: This corruption is all about receipts. When no receipts are required or receipts can be tampered with, corruption flourishes. NFT tokens & cryptocurrency networks are meant to stop this corruption by ensuring the validation of receipts & the identity of all parties in the transactions that cannot be altered or tampered with after the transaction. If the UKR govt wants to stop this persistent corruption, that is how they do so. Require all state projects whether central government, provincial, or local to create wallets for each project and generate NFT tokens for all transactions used for those specific projects with all 3rd parties that will be processed on the UKR central govt blockchains ledgers. Then transparency will be the deterrence for this persistent corruption.

Did you know? 🤔

The globe celebrates Bitcoin Pizza Day on May 22. The day honors the first transaction using cryptocurrency to pay for goods in the real world. Coincidentally, pizza was the first thing to be purchased with cryptocurrency.

On May 22, 2010, Laszlo Hanyecz ordered two Papa John's pizzas and paid the delivery fee in 10,000 Bitcoins. The two pizzas cost $10,000 nine months after the first purchase, but by 2015, they were worth an astounding $2.4 million. The two pizzas are worth $630 million since the peak price of Bitcoin was $63,000 in 2021.

#Bitcoin Could Slip Below $26k As Market Analysts Predict Further Downward Movement

Bitcoin could drop below the $26k level soon as market experts predict the leading cryptocurrency to test the $24k support level in the near term.

TL;DR
- Bitcoin is trading just above $26,200 after losing more than 1% of its value in the last 24 hours.
- Market experts predict that Bitcoin could slip toward the $24k level as the bearish trend thickens.

Bitcoin Could Drop To $24k
The cryptocurrency market has been in a bearish mode since the start of the week. Bitcoin is currently struggling to maintain its position above the $26k level. At press time, BTC is trading at $26,221, down by more than 1% over the last 24 hours.

So far this week, Bitcoin has lost more than 4% of its value and is expected to record further losses in the near term. Since the start of the month, BTC has lost 10% of its value, thanks to renewed hawkish Fed bets, the recovery in the dollar index, and the ongoing debt ceiling talks.

Alternative asset management firm Valkyrie Investments predicts that Bitcoin could drop to the $24k level as Bitcoin's daily chart Ichimoku cloud, a momentum indicator, has flipped bearish.

Analysts at Valkyrie, led by Chief Investment Officer Steven McClurg, wrote that;

"This suggests an ongoing high-timeframe bullish trend with a decline in bullish momentum and the potential for near-term retrenchment. A price close within the cloud is suggestive of losing cloud support and triggers the possibility of traversing to the opposite [lower] edge of the cloud. In this case, an Edge-to-Edge trade would bring prices to around $24,000."

Bitcoin has failed to test the $30k psychological level in recent weeks, and it is expected to drop lower over the coming days and weeks.

1661718984582987777.name: @WhiteSwapFi
1661718984582987777.text:
Liquidity pools on decentralized exchanges (#DEX) are created by users who contribute their cryptocurrency holdings. These pools facilitate trading by keeping assets within reach for traders. So traders can easily swap one token for another using the pool (instead of waiting for another trader). Every trading pair on DEX has its own liquidity pool.

Meanwhile, liquidity providers earn fees based on their contribution to the pool. So, everyone gets a benefit: traders can swap tokens anytime, and liquidity providers get their swap fees.
#WhiteSwapDEX

It is just Apple's policy on financial and cryptocurrency-related apps.

Apple will only allows apps that deal with cryptocurrencies under certain conditions.

'Cryptocurrency apps may not offer currency for completing tasks, such as downloading other apps, encouraging other users to download, posting to social networks, etc." according to them

Apple is also requesting that any cryptocurrency app should come from established banks, securities firms, futures commission merchants ("FCM"), or other approved financial institutions. And, most importantly, they should be lawful.

Even though you app may fulfil all I have listed above, you can simple double check these to potentially resolve this issue:

Company Verification: Ensure that your organisation is properly established and verified as a recognised financial institution or cryptocurrency exchange provider. You might be asked to provide all necessary legal documentation to prove your status.

Seller and Company Name: The name under which the app is being published must match the legal name of the established financial institution or cryptocurrency exchange provider. 

This means that the name of your Apple Developer account must be the name of your exchange or financial institution. If it's not, you'll need to change your Apple Developer account name to match the legal name of your company.

Legal Compliance: Your app must also comply with all local laws in the regions where it's available. This includes any regulations regarding the transmission of virtual currency. You may need to consult with a legal professional to ensure you're in compliance.

Clear Explanation: Make sure your app description is clear about what your app does and what it doesn’t do. If there are misconceptions about the purpose of your app, this can lead to issues with the review process.

Re-submit: There could still be some back-and-forth with the Apple review team, as this is not a guarantee that your app will be published.
